SIMPLE: dimissory
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dimissory
<hw>Dim"is*so*ry</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dimissorius</ets>: cf. F. <ets>dimissoire</ets>. See
<er>Dimit</er>.]</ety> <def>Sending away; dismissing to another
jurisdiction; granting leave to depart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Letters dimissory</b></col> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>,
<cd>letters given by a bishop dismissing a person who is removing into
another diocese, and recommending him for reception there.</cd>
<rj><au>Hook.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dimit</ent>⟦br⟧
